[SN]TITLE[SN]
ICYMI: Valley stocks take a beating

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
In Case You Missed It: a round-up of interesting technology-related links shared over the weekend.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Here are Silicon Valley's big losers
Silicon Valley companies took a hammering in the markets last week - spooked, the Silicon Valley Business Journal says, by instability in the Chinese economy. The Journal has rounded up the biggest losers in the Valley.
Google wants to help you post food photos on Maps
As if some people needed more encouragement, Google is testing out an idea that would make it easier for people to attach food pictures to Google Map locations, bolstering its restaurant reviews.
Tesla partners with AirBnB, subsidises chargers
High end AirBnB properties may soon come with a Tesla charging point. Tesla is putting up the money for several locations in California.
Pro-government Twitter bots try to hush Mexican activists
An interesting look at how Twitter bots - which Wired describes as pro-government - drowned out dissenting voices in Mexico.
